    <section id="section_hbg_wfj_2v">
      <title>Resources for learning DITA:</title>
      <p>If you want to start learning about DITA in general there is a web site called <xref
          href="https://www.learningdita.com/" format="html" scope="external">Learning
        DITA</xref>.</p>
      <p><xref href="https://stefan-jung.org/dita-introduction/"
					format="html" scope="external">DITA Introduction</xref> articles by Stefan Jung.</p>
      <p>The free Oxygen <xref
          href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-addons/topics/live-tutorials-addon.html"
          format="html" scope="external">Live Tutorials add-on</xref> contains various small
        tutorials for learning DITA.</p>
      <p>The DITA 1.3 standard specification can be found here: <xref
          href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/dita/1.3/specs/#introduction/dita-release-overview.html"
          format="html" scope="external"/>.</p>
      <p>There are also a number of good books like <xref
          href="http://xmlpress.net/publications/dita/practitioners-1/" format="html"
          scope="external">DITA For Practitioners</xref> and the <xref
          href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/dita/styleguide/" format="html" scope="external">DITA
          Style Guide</xref>.</p>
      <p><xref href="https://acm-sigdoc-structured.org/1-curriculum-resources.html" format="html"
          scope="external">Resources for understanding and working with DITA XML by ACM</xref>.</p>
      <p><xref href="https://github.com/wongyah/awesome-technical-writing-learning" format="html"
          scope="external">List of resources for learning and experimenting with DITA content by
          Yedda Wang</xref></p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_ufb_ngj_2v">
      <title>Resources for customizing the DITA output formats</title>
      <p>Usually customizing the XHTML based outputs means creating your custom CSS selectors. If
                you generate WebHelp output using Oxygen, we have a section explaining basic <xref
                  href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/wh-responsive-customization-tips.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">WebHelp customizations</xref>.</p>
      <p>For PDF-based outputs we recommend, support and maintain our <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/pdf-css-customization.html"
        format="html" scope="external">CSS-based PDF publishing</xref> which is free to use from <ph
        keyref="oxygen"/>. There are also a number of different choices to obtain PDF from DITA:
        <xref href="ditaToPDF.dita"/>.</p>
            <p>We have a series of past webinar recordings about customizing the published output:<ul>
                    <li>Transforming DITA documents to PDF using CSS<ul>
                            <li><xref
                                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2021/webinar_transforming_dita_documents_to_pdf_part_1.html"
                                    format="html" scope="external">Part 1 – Page Definitions, Cover
                                    Page and PDF Metadata</xref></li>
                            <li><xref
                                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2022/webinar_transforming_dita_documents_to_pdf_using_css_part_2.html"
                                    format="html" scope="external">Part 2 – Book design, Pagination,
                                    Page Layout and Bookmarks</xref></li>
                            <li><xref
                                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2022/webinar_transforming_dita_documents_to_pdf_using_css_part_3.html"
                                    format="html" scope="external">Part 3 – Advanced Fonts
                                    Usage</xref></li>
                            <li><xref
                                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2023/webinar_transforming_dita_documents_to_pdf_using_css_part_4.html"
                                    format="html" scope="external">Part 4 – Advanced CSS
                                    Rules</xref></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li><xref
                            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2022/webinar_techniques_for_customizing_the_webhelp_responsive_output.html"
                            format="html" scope="external">Techniques for Customizing the WebHelp
                            Responsive Output</xref></li>
                    <li><xref
                            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/events/2022/webinar_using_oxygen_styles_basket_to_create_css_customization_from_scratch.html"
                            format="html" scope="external">Using Oxygen Styles Basket to Create CSS
                            Customization from Scratch</xref></li>
                </ul>And if you are interested in server side building and publishing this topic
                might be useful:<xref href="server_side_building_and_publishing.dita"/>.</p>
    </section>
